I'm afraid you're going to be left alone with this idea, friends.
It's just right.
If some Mexicans are not yet prepared to forgive the United States for the way they treated Mexico a century and a half ago, then they have to accept the fact that some Mexican-Americans are still resentful of how their relatives were treated much less time ago.
I'm not going to.
